# Favorite Slot Rules

## Canonical blank check
Always use `FavoriteUtils.is_blank_favorite(fav)` — never `BasicHelpers.is_blank_favorite` (removed).

A slot is blank **only when GPS is blank/nil AND `locked == false`**.  
A locked slot is **never** blank, even if its GPS is the sentinel value.

```lua
-- ❌ BAD — ignores locked state
if not fav or fav.gps == nil or fav.gps == BLANK_GPS then ...

-- ✅ GOOD
if FavoriteUtils.is_blank_favorite(fav) then ...
```

## Auto-assign skips locked slots
`FavoriteUtils.is_blank_favorite` already excludes locked slots, so no extra `and not fav.locked` guard is needed when scanning for the first available slot.

## Tag deletion must clear lock
When a chart tag is deleted, the matching favorite slot must have **both** its GPS reset to `BLANK_GPS` and its `locked` field set to `false`.

The canonical path is `tag_destroy_helper.cleanup_player_favorites(tag)`, which is called unconditionally (not gated on `faved_by_players`) so it catches stale tracking arrays.

`prune_stale_favorites(player, surface_index, pfaves)` in `fave_bar.lua` is the GUI-side safety net that runs at build time and enforces the same invariant.

## Lock toggle guard
`toggle_favorite_lock` must reject blank slots using `FavoriteUtils.is_blank_favorite` so that a slot with blank GPS and `locked == true` (an illegal state) can still be unlocked.
